  "notes": "Low German (Plattdeutsch / Nedderdütsch). Descended from Old Saxon — NOT from Old High German. DID NOT UNDERGO the High German Consonant Shift: maken vs. German machen; water vs. German Wasser. Closely related to Dutch, Frisian, and Old English. Extremely diverse dialects across northern Germany and Netherlands. Now mostly spoken by elderly; listed as 'vulnerable' by UNESCO. Source: Gallée (1993), Robinson (1992).",
